

Write a program that takes a number n as input and prints nth number in Fibonacci series. The Fibonacci series is a sequence of numbers in which each number is the sum of the two preceding numbers. The sequence starts with 0 and 1, and then each subsequent number is the sum of the two numbers before it. So, the first few numbers in the series are - 0, 1, 1, 2, 3, 5, 8, 13.

Input Format

Read the integer n, which denotes the position in the Fibonacci sequence.

The program efficiently handles large values of ùëõ using iterative computation.
Output Format

Print the nth Fibonacci number.
Sample Input 0

4
Sample Output 0

2
=========================================================================================================================
public class Solution {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        /* Enter your code here. Read input from STDIN. Print output to STDOUT. Your class should be named Solution. */
        Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
        int n=sc.nextInt();
        int a=0;
        if(n==1)
        {
            System.out.print(a);
            return;
        }
        int b=1;
        if(n==2)
        {
            System.out.print(b);
            return;
        }
        int c=0;
        int temp;
        for(int i=3;i<=n;i++)
        {
            c=a+b;
            a=b;
            b=c;
        }
        System.out.print(c);
    }
}
